Pico 5 active firmware: color-coded button sequence.

This folder is the active Pico 5 project. The old phone/window prop code is archived in:

../../pico6-unused-future-puzzles/unused-future-puzzles/

Hardware:
- GPIO 15: red button
- GPIO 16: green button
- GPIO 17: yellow button
- GPIO 18: blue button

Main topics:
- Publishes escape/pico5/color_sequence_complete
- Publishes escape/pico5/color_sequence_error
- Subscribes escape/cmd/all/status_request
- Subscribes escape/cmd/all/reset_puzzle

The color-button sequence listens from startup/reset. The attempt timeout starts
only after the first button press so the puzzle can sit ready without playing
an error cue. Each press is checked immediately when the button input goes LOW,
then that button re-arms when the input returns HIGH.

If the next button does not match the ordered code, the Pico immediately
publishes escape/pico5/color_sequence_error and clears the current attempt.
The Raspberry Pi plays try-again.wav on the 1st, 4th, 7th, etc. wrong entry
and buzzer.mp3 on the two wrong entries between those.

Required ordered code:
- R R R
- G G G G
- Y Y
- B B B
